<Author>pablot
<Content>Oasis of Calm I stayed at The Seehof for 3 nights when on business in Berlin. Rooms were on the small side but have everything you want as well as being immauculatley clean. They had an extensive menu and the food was excellent. What was also a real treat was the lovely outside patio that overlooked a small lake, very calming and relaxing after a busy day. One thing I would pick out for special mention was the the staff...they were absolutley superb. Nothing was too much trouble, their English was excellent and every one had a smile on their faces. The reason I stayed here was becasue all the 5 star hotels were full for a big trade fair in town, the reasons I will return are obvious. 
